    "Decision Tree method holds significant appeal in the context of classifying fruits based on their maturity levels, primarily owing to its simplicity and interpretability (Mim et al., 2018).",
    "The literature supports its higher predictive accuracy for fruit classification, as evidenced in (Fadchar & Cruz, 2020; Mim et al., 2018; Suresha et al., 2012).",
    "Random Forest Random Forest is a machine learning approach that leverages an ensemble of decision trees to predict outcomes.",
    "It trains multiple decision trees in parallel and determines the final decision based on the majority consensus of these trees.",
    "Random Forest employs bootstrapping to train each decision tree on different subsets of the training data (Misra & Li, 2019), ensuring diversity and reducing variance."
